6. Decision Rights

Governance defines:

Who Can
Create standards
Approve access
Define quality thresholds
Resolve conflicts
Approve changes

Without clear decision rights, governance fails.

7. Data Policies

Policies define required behavior.

Examples:

Data must have an owner.
Sensitive data must be classified.
Customer data quality score must exceed 95%.

Good policies are:

Clear
Enforceable
Measurable
Business aligned
8. Data Standards

Standards support policy implementation.

Examples:

Naming Standards

Customer_ID

instead of

CustNo

Data Definition Standards

Consistent business meaning.

Quality Standards

Accuracy > 98%

Completeness > 95%

9. Data Governance Processes
Policy Management

Create and maintain policies.

Issue Management

Identify and resolve data problems.

Change Management

Manage governance changes.

Compliance Monitoring

Verify adherence to standards.

Risk Management

Identify data-related risks.

